.TH "quota_send_warning" 9 "quota_send_warning" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
quota_send_warning \- Send warning to userspace about exceeded quota
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" quota_send_warning
.BI "(struct kqid qid "  ","
.BI "dev_t dev "  ","
.BI "const char warntype "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "qid" 12
The kernel internal quota identifier.
.IP "dev" 12
The device on which the fs is mounted (sb->s_dev)
.IP "warntype" 12
The type of the warning: QUOTA_NL_...
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This can be used by filesystems (including those which don't use
dquot) to send a message to userspace relating to quota limits.
